    "    \n",
    "    # Locate the rows which contain mice on each drug and get the tumor volumes\n",
    "    tumorVol = tvMergedDF.loc[tvMergedDF[\"Drug Regimen\"] == drug, \"Tumor Volume (mm3)\"]\n",

    "    # add subsets \n",
    "    tumorData.append(tumorVol)\n",
    "    \n",
    "# Determine outliers using upper and lower bounds\n",
    "    quartile = tumorVol.quantile([0.25,0.5,0.75])\n",
    "    lowQuar = quartile[0.25]\n",
    "    uppQuar = quartile[0.75]\n",
    "    iqr = uppQuar - lowQuar\n",
    "    lowBound = lowQuar - (1.5*iqr)\n",
    "    uppBound = uppQuar + (1.5*iqr)\n",
    "    outlier = tumorVol.loc[(tumorVol >= uppBound) | (tumorVol <= lowBound)]\n",
    "    print(f\"{drug} outlier: \\n{outlier}\")"

    "# Calculate the correlation coefficient and linear regression model \n",
    "# for mouse weight and average tumor volume for the Capomulin regimen\n",
    "\n",
    "#establish x and y values and find St. Pearson Correlation Coefficient for Mouse Weight and Tumor Volume Avg\n",
    "correlation = round(st.pearsonr(capAvg[\"Weight (g)\"], capAvg[\"Tumor Volume (mm3)\"])[0], 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "#print St. Pearson Correlation Coefficient\n",
    "print(f\"The correlation between the two factors is {correlation:.2f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# establish linear regression values\n",
    "x_values = capAvg[\"Weight (g)\"]\n",
    "y_values = capAvg[\"Tumor Volume (mm3)\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "# linear regression line \n",
    "regval = st.linregress(x_values , y_values)\n",
    "# print(regval)\n",
    "Yval =  capAvg[\"Weight (g)\"] * regval[0] + regval[1]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# scatter plot of the data\n",
